HEADWORD: Widmanstätten figures
<hw>Wid"man*st⟦aum⟧t`ten fig"ures</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>. <fld>(Min.)</fld>
<def>Certain figures appearing on etched meteoric iron; -- so called
after <person>A. B. <etsep>Widmanst⟦aum⟧tten</etsep></person>, of
<city>Vienna</city>, who first described them in 1808. See the Note and
<xex>Illust.</xex> under <er>Meteorite</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Widow</ent>⟦br⟧
